==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Elastin
<hw>E*las"tin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Elast</ets>ic
+ <ets>-in</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol. Chem.)</fld> <def>A nitrogenous
substance, somewhat resembling albumin, which forms the chemical basis
of elastic tissue. It is very insoluble in most fluids, but is gradually
dissolved when digested with either pepsin or trypsin.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elastoplast</ent>⟦br⟧
